In fact, cats can only see in conditions with some light, such as:

* Low light conditions (e.g., moonlight, starlight)
* Low light conditions with some ambient light (e.g., a dimly lit room)
* Conditions with some light from a distant source (e.g., a moonlit night)

But in complete darkness, they can't see at all.
